[thinking] **Exploring testing implications**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m considering whether to use version 6.0.0 instead of the latest version. There’s a potential issue with nativeTestCompile due to the JUnit 6 @ClassTemplate annotation possibly causing UnsupportedFeature. The user will likely inform me about this. Tests should run under Native Image by default. I wonder if the native executable includes classes in the image heap. During a native test run, the build/classes/java/test directory may still exist. I'm mulling over how class loading works in this context.
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Analyzing Class.forName in native images**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m exploring whether the native image supports Class.forName for registered classes. It seems like test classes are likely included, which could work well. The native image doesn’t support dynamic class definitions, but known classes via Class.forName should be okay. A potential issue could arise during scanning, as it examines all test classes. I need to verify if the @ClassTemplate allows method tests — according to JUnit 6 documentation, it appears to be an annotation used with a registered provider and may not be directly executable.
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Simplifying test class scanning**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m realizing the actual test method within the class will run only once. It scans itself and collects nested classes, which is great! I could simplify things by defining an inner public static class called ScannedClassTemplate instead of using the top-level test class as @ClassTemplate. While the current setup is okay, I need to consider a potential compile error regarding the @ClassTemplate annotation, which might be experimental. Also, I should check if the class field order adheres to existing style guidelines!
[thinking] 
