setup is okay, I need to consider a potential compile error regarding the @ClassTemplate annotation, which might be experimental. Also, I should check if the class field order adheres to existing style guidelines!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Fixed the compilation issue by adding the correct JUnit 6 test dependencies needed for `@ClassTemplate` support in:\n\n- `tests/src/org.springframework/spring-test/7.0.0/build.gradle`\n\nAdded:\n\n```groovy\ntestImplementation platform('org.junit:junit-bom:6.0.0')\ntestImplementation 'org.junit.jupiter:junit-jupiter'\ntestRuntimeOnly 'org.junit.platform:junit-platform-launcher'\n```\n\nThis should make `org.junit.jupiter.api.ClassTemplate` and the related class-template extension APIs available for `TestClassScannerTest.java`.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0189db8303069f10016a29d5725e2c8196a581b1f9db0acd8a\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1593, "output": 640, "cacheRead": 54784, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 57017, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781126496920, "responseId": "resp_0189db8303069f10016a29d561864881968775cfe05c67aba7"}}
